## Step 2 — Add the Handler Function

**File:** `common/chat.cpp`  
**Anchor:** After the closing `}` of `common_chat_params_init_gigachat_v3` at line 1517, before `namespace workaround {` at line 1519.

Insert between lines 1517 and 1519:

```cpp
static common_chat_params common_chat_params_init_mistral_instruct_v3(
        const common_chat_template &          tmpl,
        const autoparser::generation_params & inputs) {
    common_chat_params data;

    data.prompt            = common_chat_template_direct_apply_impl(tmpl, inputs);
    data.format            = COMMON_CHAT_FORMAT_PEG_NATIVE;
    data.supports_thinking = false;
    data.preserved_tokens  = {
        "[TOOL_CALLS]",
    };

    auto has_tools       = inputs.tools.is_array() && !inputs.tools.empty();
    auto include_grammar = has_tools && inputs.tool_choice != COMMON_CHAT_TOOL_CHOICE_NONE;

    auto parser = build_chat_peg_parser([&](common_chat_peg_builder & p) {
        if (!has_tools || inputs.tool_choice == COMMON_CHAT_TOOL_CHOICE_NONE) {
            include_grammar = false;
            return p.literal(inputs.generation_prompt) + p.content(p.rest());
        }

        // Mistral Nemo tool call format:
        //   [TOOL_CALLS][{"name": "func", "arguments": {...}, "id": "123456789"}]
        // The section_start "[TOOL_CALLS][" already includes the opening '[' of the JSON
        // array, so array_wrapped = false (brackets are part of the section markers).
        auto tool_calls = p.standard_json_tools(
            /* section_start     = */ "[TOOL_CALLS][",
            /* section_end       = */ "]",
            /* tools             = */ inputs.tools,
            /* parallel          = */ inputs.parallel_tool_calls,
            /* force             = */ inputs.tool_choice == COMMON_CHAT_TOOL_CHOICE_REQUIRED,
            /* name_key          = */ "name",
            /* args_key          = */ "arguments",
            /* array_wrapped     = */ false,
            /* function_is_key   = */ false,
            /* call_id_key       = */ "id",
            /* gen_call_id_key   = */ "",
            /* parameters_order  = */ {"name", "arguments", "id"});

        // Content runs up to the optional [TOOL_CALLS] section.
        // p.content(p.until("[TOOL_CALLS]")) matches empty when tool_choice == REQUIRED
        // and the model outputs a tool call immediately.
        return p.literal(inputs.generation_prompt) +
               p.content(p.until("[TOOL_CALLS]")) +
               tool_calls + p.end();
    });

    data.parser = parser.save();

    if (include_grammar) {
        data.grammar_lazy = has_tools && inputs.tool_choice == COMMON_CHAT_TOOL_CHOICE_AUTO;
        data.grammar = build_grammar([&](const common_grammar_builder & builder) {
            foreach_function(inputs.tools, [&](const json & tool) {
                const auto & function = tool.at("function");
                auto         schema   = function.at("parameters");
                builder.resolve_refs(schema);
            });
            parser.build_grammar(builder, data.grammar_lazy);
        });
        data.grammar_triggers = {
            { COMMON_GRAMMAR_TRIGGER_TYPE_WORD, "[TOOL_CALLS]" }
        };
    }

    return data;
}
```

**Key design notes:**
- `standard_json_tools` is called with `section_start = "[TOOL_CALLS]["` — the `[` that opens the JSON array is embedded in the prefix (same pattern as the Cohere test in `test-chat-auto-parser.cpp`).
- `parameters_order = {"name", "arguments", "id"}` matches Nemo's Jinja which serializes `function|tojson` (giving `name` + `arguments`) then appends `"id"` last.
- `p.content(p.until("[TOOL_CALLS]"))` gracefully handles REQUIRED tool choice — if the model outputs `[TOOL_CALLS]` immediately, `until` matches the empty string and the content node is empty.
- No `p.end()` in the content-only path (matches pattern in other content-only handlers).

---

## Step 3 — Add the Detection Condition

**File:** `common/chat.cpp`  
**Anchor:** After the GigaChat block closing `}` at line 1688, before `return std::nullopt;` at line 1690.

Insert between lines 1688 and 1690:

